<userid>107983317628364224866< /userid>< name>
The Dove<//name>
<Time>1587668079065< /Time>< rating>
5<//rating>
< review>
I can't possibly say enough good things to describe the team at Toluca Lake Dentistry. After years of easy visits, I got clobbered during the COVID-19 pandemic with excruciating pain under a 3-tooth bridge. Facing the prospect of a long wait, I texted Roxanna in desperation at 1 a.m. on a Sunday night and she called back at 6 a.m. to get me in to see the doctor first thing. Roxanna has been managing the practice for as long as I can remember--at least 37 years. She knows absolutely everything, from dentistry to billing, and she's got a great sense of humor too, which makes her the perfect liaison between patients and the doctor. Dr. McKay combines the perfect balance of precision, efficiency, and knowledge to handle even the most complicated situations. He also takes the time answer any questions and to explain what he is doing and why, which I find very helpful. He initially attempted a root canal by drilling through the bridge, the most conservative remedy, but found it was impossible because the acidic nature of the root infection neutralized the numbing agent (alkaline). A further complication was that the second root had calcified over, making it impossible to view in an x-ray or safely drill without risking disaster. So Dr. McKay shifted to plan-B, which was to remove the existing bridge and a neighboring crown, extract the tooth, disinfect the area, and create a 4-tooth bridge. This completely solved the problem and left me with a quick, painless recovery. The entire staff at Toluca Lake Dentistry is friendly and proficient in best methods in this state-of-the-art facility. Each person is a master in their area of specialization and they work together as a well-coordinated team to solve any dental issue. Dentistry is expensive, so it pays to go to a team that gets it right the first time. I'd give them 10 stars if I could!<//review>

Hate to do this. Never leave bad reviews, but they left me no choice; so I rather make sure future patrons have the transparency I wasn't afforded. Upon booking an appointment online; I was contacted to make sure that my Insurance carrier was accepted (I get it, then need to make sure they're covered before wasting they're time) I submitted my info, green pass go. what they failed to tell me was that while its accepted , its out side of my network, so I would have out of pocket costs. Through out the visit I was asked multiple times 'how did you hear about us' etc. to which I responded every time that it was just convenience as I live down the street. There were multiple times times where they could have been transparent with me about my insurance. True, in the end I could have known better so its my fault, but it speaks volumes to how they do business: *before you enter lets make sure your insurance clears......if it does'nt pay in full; doesnt matter, they got theirs you'll figure out the rest* reeks of desperation and nickel and diming. There charges didn't reflect what my insurances did, to which I called and found out they made a mistake. on top of which they added a PPE fee after the fact. Anthony said he saw that on his end too, so we could wait a little bit and he would check back with me.
I decided to call 888BESTBUY to try to find out where my order was. After a little bit of digging and calling around, I was assured by a lady over the phone that my order was on the truck and ready for delivery and installation; That the ETA was 2:30pm.

<Text>I've been going to this best buy for gaming headsets for the past four years. Not only do they have great gaming headsets but they have an excellent two year replacement plan for them.

Just today I returned a headset I had a warranty on and they accepted it and let me put the money of not only the headset but the protection plan towards the new headset I was going to get. It was a fast and easy process and the man helping me was very sweet.

The unfortunate part was they no longer carried the exact same model of headset I am rather fond of, but I was able to easily get help from one of the on floor associates to see if there was any of that headset around at other stores, there wasn't so I went with the next best thing that was closest to the price of the headset I'd gotten.

<username>Margaret Odamo< /username><Date>1512776760342<//Date>< Review>
I decided to use the best buy 18 months interest free financing to purchase about $4200 worth of appliances on november 6th. Delivery was scheduled for november 9th.
I  called back the next day to change the delivery address (forgot to say I am moving from an apartment to my new house), they said since i changed the address the delivery window was no longer available (both addresses about 2.5 miles apart) and would have to be rescheduled.

Rescheduled for the following week between 8-12pm. no one showed up, driver calls to say "oh i have 12-4". I said no, was already on my way to go empty out old apartment, so had to toss all my frozen stuff.
went to best buy, cancelled the transaction and gave them back the free google chrome.
Someone called Angie called and I agreed to get re-delivery on the 24th.
delivery went smooth, no issues. all is well, then I get an  email from best buy credit card (CITI) today and they say "you missed  the first payment on december 2nd so you are charged a late fee" I went ape nuts.

I  dont have a bill yet, how can I be late, I had even written a letter to them saying my purchase date was changed to the 24th not the 6th. they say they only go by the order date, irrespective of wether you actually receive the items.  I refused to pay the late fee, paid the balance off and closed the account.
The one star is for their staff (they were all great) and the products (love my whirlpool washer, dryer and samsung fridge, also got a dyson vaccum cleaner and iphone x).  the entire experience was tedious and stressfull, I had been thinking of making best buy my go-to place for stuff but i think ill stick with amazon.<//Review>

<user>111529243739417573025<//user><Name>BrotherKehn (BrotherKehn)</Name><Time>1444862893538</Time><rating>4</rating>< Text>
Location is a bit hidden in the Mcarthy Ranch area. Being near by the waste business at 237 freeway, I usually walk quick to get into the store because the air reeks really bad and when I would finish shopping, I would rush to my car for the same reason. The place is sometimes dead but, that means usually their products are in stock then. Save yourself some time, call to check if what ever item you want is in stock before driving up there. The service is great, sucks that they can't really help you with credit card issues like increasing the limit, they only can sign you up for it. Citi Bank is the credit issuer towards their store credit card so, look out for that. Till then, their employees are friendly and helpful, sometimes they look like theyre over working for a somewhat empty store.< /Text>

103136226799416260286</user>
<user_name>Ryan Sampson<//user_name><date>1472077893752< /date><rate>5</rate>< text>
Long story long I arrived on bad terms and left on good terms. After coming to the understanding that the warranty for my problem was up to the manufacturer Lenovo and not a liability of Best Buy, the Geek Squad associate Kevin politely informed me that anything that could be done to fix the problem immediately would be over his head, as the problem was with a workstation urgency was present. In steps the General Manager Kellie Adams.

She laid out what Best Buy policies are and being an understanding person I accepted that I bought a low-end computer and we got what we paid for. What she did say was that she would do whatever was in her power to make sure that I walked out that door happy.

The positive attitude of Kevin and Kellie turned me from being someone that did not plan on ever coming back to Best Buy to someone who walked out the door with a purchase of two new workstations. I have a growing company and I know where I will be going for hardware from now on.

It's easy to find the motivation to write a bad review, it takes a lot for me to find it worth my time to write a positive one. If management is reading this take notes.< /text>
